    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>There is a certain parallel to ἄκακος in the English expression not bad, which in many contexts indicates something which is positively good. In fact, with certain intonation the expression not bad may actually have a stronger positive designation than good.</Content>
    </Note>
